## Tiered workflow (S / A / B / C)

All work: branch, PR, tests, and lint. Tier sets ceremony and who merges.

| Tier | Scope | Flow | Review |
|------|-------|------|--------|
| **S** | Schema, security, infra, auth, deploy | Full ceremony | Human review |
| **A** | Features (new capability, API, integration) | Issue + PR | Human review |
| **B** | Enhancements to existing behavior | PR | Auto-merge if CI green |
| **C** | Trivial (docs, typos, comments) | PR | Auto-merge if CI green |

Conventional commits: `feat|fix|docs|refactor|test|chore|ci|perf: description`

## Guardrails

**NEVER:** Drop or wipe databases; delete infrastructure (Makefile, CI, deploy scripts); push to `main`; skip tests to save time; store secrets or commit credentials; leave TODO/FIXME/HACK in committed code; add ghost implementations (unwired or untested code).

**ALWAYS:** Run tests before and after changes; update `.github/context/` when architecture or public surface changes; verify every import resolves; keep functions under 50 lines; prefer editing existing files over adding new ones.

